Legg Mason to Combine Alts Manager Permal with EnTrust              DailyAltsLiquid Alternatives | News, Data and AnalysisTwitterLinkedInFacebookGoogle+RSSHOMENEWSCompany NewsFund NewsIndustry NewsInvesting InsightsPeople NewsSurveys & RankingsCOMMENTARYRESEARCHVIDEOSDailyAlts VideosFUNDSAlternative BetaAlternative Fixed IncomeAlternative IncomeArbitrageCommoditiesLong/Short CommoditiesGlobal MacroHedged EquityCovered CallsHedged Equity – OtherLong/Short EquityLow Volatility EquityLiquid AlternativesManaged FuturesMarket NeutralMulti-StrategyOther13F ReplicationReal ReturnReal EstateRisk ParityTBDEVENTSRESOURCESPODCASTEDUCATION      Legg Mason to Combine Alts Manager Permal with EnTrustBy Brian Haskin | February 11, 2016 Leave a CommentMergers and acquisitions (“M&A”) activity within the alternative investments industry was very strong in 2015 and has continued at an unabated pace into the New Year. One of the many recent mergers involved EnTrust Capital and Permal Group, the latter of which is Legg Mason’s hedge-fund platform subsidiary that was purchased by Legg Mason in 2005.Under the terms of the transaction, Legg Mason will own 65% of the combined firm, to be known as EnTrustPermal, with the remainder to be owned by EnTrust co-founder and Managing Partner Gregg Hymowitz.“The combination of EnTrust and Permal creates a powerful organization in the hedge fund universe,” said Mr. Hymowitz, in a statement issued by Legg Mason. “The complementary nature of our investment strategies, geographies and global investor/partner base dramatically springboards us over our competition.”Greater Scale and ResourcesAs a result of the merger, the new firm’s scale, resources, and global investment talent will be able to deliver proprietary investments to over 700 institutional accounts and a “significant number” of high-net-worth investors, according to Mr. Hymowitz. The combination of the two firms will create a platform with expanded alternative capabilities and offerings, including:More than 55 investment professionalsOver 150 unique investment offerings across 18 different strategiesAn expansive platform ranging from “opportunistic co-investments” to “tail-risk hedging strategies” and “bespoked” customized investment solutionsMore proprietary investment opportunitiesDirect hedge funds and private debt offeringsA broadened Managed Account platform“The combined EnTrustPermal brings together two leading names in the alternative space, creating a significant potential growth engine for Legg Mason,” said Legg Mason CEO and Chairman Joseph Sullivan. “The team at EnTrust has a proven track record for driving significant organic growth through product innovation, with over 20% growth annually since the financial crisis. We see meaningful opportunities to combine this innovation with Permal’s blue chip client base, product offering and global footprint.”Deal to Close in Mid-2016The deal, which is expected to close in mid-2016, should be modestly accretive to Legg Mason’s earnings that year, excluding restructuring and transition charges, which are estimated at $100 million. Ultimately, Legg Mason expects EnTrustPermal to achieve cost savings of between $35 million and $40 million per year.Permal is the manager of two multi-alternative mutual funds:Permal Alternative Core Fund (LPTIX) launched in April 2009 and allocates its assets across alternative and traditional asset classes. The fund ranks in the 26th, 16th and 9th percentiles over the past 1, 3 and 5-year periods ending January 31, 2016.Permal Alternative Select Fund (PASWX) launched in February 2014 and allocates its assets to hedged equity, event driven and global macro strategies. For the year ending January 31, 2016, the fund returned -9.23%, ranking it in the bottom 14% of funds in its Morningstar category.Past performance does not necessarily predict future results.Jason Seagraves contributed to this article. Related Links: Permal Alternative Core Fund ▪ Permal Alternative Select Fun